3.4 Product and Patent Benchmarks 
To benchmark potential tether deployment solutions, we began by reviewing historical and contemporary 
tether satellite missions. This discovery process included examining systems from early demonstrations such 
as Gemini XI (1966) to more advanced concepts like YES2 (ESA, 2007) and Aalto-1 Plasma Brake (2017вАУ2022). 
By analyzing these missions, we identified common deployment mechanisms, their operational challenges, 
and their adaptability to CubeSat-scale constraints. Table 3.4.1 summarizes the pros and cons of each 
deployment style along with their heritage. 
