7 Deliver Phase: Concept Analysis 
7.1 Design Analysis 
Tether Wire Storage Capacity of Spool 
The spool was designed with 40 mm side flanges and a 150 mm long and 20 mm diameter axle. Once the 
tether wire was selected to have a diameter of 2.05 mm, the total length of wire that the spool could store had 
to be calculated to ensure the 150 meters requirement for generating Martian gravity was met. First, the total 
volume of space between the axle and flanges of the spool (where tether wire would be stored) was calculated 
as shown below. 
Outer spool radius: ro = 0.04 m 
Inner spool radius: ri = 0.01 m 
Reel length: hr = 0.15 m 
Reel volume: рЭСЙаѓ• = рЭЬЛ вИЧ рЭСЯаѓ•аѓҐ
ађґ вИЧ вДОаѓ• вИТ рЭЬЛ вИЧ рЭСЯаѓ•аѓЬ
ађґ вИЧ вДОаѓ•
 = рЭЬЛ вИЧ (0.04 m)ађґ вИЧ 0.15 m вИТ рЭЬЛ вИЧ (0.01 m)ађґ вИЧ 0.15 m 
= 7.0686 x 10-4 m3
With the spool volume known, the maximum length of the tether wire that could be stored in that space 
was calculated by setting the volume of the spool equal to the volume of the wire and solving for the length of 
the wire. 
