Level wind bidirectional thread pitch 
The level wind bidirectional thread needs to have a thread pitch that, despite being driven with a 5:1 gear 
ratio, only moves the carriage over 1 wire diameter per rotation of the spool to ensure the tightest possible 
packing factor. With a known wire diameter of 2.05mm, the pitch can be calculated. 
