Frame Rod Analysis 
The 3U CubeSat frame is made up of four OTS rectangular rods made from Aluminum 6061 T-6. Based on 
the positioning of the frame within the total CubeSat, these rods are mounted perpendicular to the launch 
direction, meaning a distributed launch force acts on each rod individually. This launch load can be modeled 
in the diagram below. 
Figure 7.1.1: Launch Load Frame Rod FBD 
A launch force of 6g was chosen as a conservative estimate of the force acting on the CubeSat system as 
the satellite is launched into low Earth orbit. The force acting upon each rod is detailed in the calculations 
below. 
