Bolt and Joint Analysis 
On the 3U CubeSAT frame, a total of 8 bolts were used to thread into 4 rectangular cross-section aluminum 
6064-T1 rods. The bolts chosen to be used were M3 X 0.5 Class 12.9 Alloy Steel bolts [2] because that size 
would allow for a 1 mm wall thickness from the thread in the bars. Designed to a factor of safety of 1.2, the 
necessary pre-load and tightening torque of each bolt was calculated. The analysis was completed assuming 
a preload target of an engineering standard of 70% of the yield strength. Each bolt is assumed to be in pure 
tension, with no temperature-induced relaxation as well, with the threads fully engaged. Possible failure 
modes from these bolts were considered to be failure in shear, failure from thread stripping, or tensile failure 
due to over-tightening. A section view of the frame with the bolts is shown in Figure 7.1.2, with a free body 
diagram of the frame bolt shown in Figure 7.1.3. 

43 
