12.3 Functional Surfaces 
The following descriptions (Table 12.3.1) lists out critical surfaces within the assembly. It includes any 
surface that slides, rolls, rotates, or contacts another part within the system. The idea was to essentially 
highlight where any mechanical interaction happens which would help to identify any surfaces that may 
need a smooth finish, lubrication, or durability considerations. Not all surfaces in the system were 
deemed critical. 
