12.4 Electrical/Wiring Diagrams 
The electrical system as shown in Figure 12.4.1 displays all of the electronic components in the tether 
deployment system with their required amplifiers, controllers, and power boards and how they will be wired to 
each other. The right side which has the power board, microcontroller, servo, stepper motor and controller is 
all housed in the 3U mother satellite. The rest of the components on the left are in the 1U daughter satellite. 
All of the electronics will be powered from an external power source from the larger 12U satellites supplied to 
the power boards within each side. All electronics will be mounted to the frame of their respective satellites to 
allow for proper grounding and discharging of any static charge. The frame has aluminum sheets attached on 
all outer facing sides reducing the need for individual electronics housings. 
Figure 12.4.1: Complete Wiring Diagram of Tether System 